    "stac_version": "1.1.0",
    "description": "This collection contains the raw panchromatic (PAN) bands from the SPOT 2, 4, and 5 satellites for Brazil circa 2008. The panchromatic sensor provides the highest native spatial resolution of the missions, capturing light across a broad visible spectrum (0.51-0.73 \u00b5m for SPOT 2, 0.61-0.68 \u00b5m for SPOT 4, and 0.48-0.71 \u00b5m for SPOT 5). These bands are intended for advanced photogrammetric analysis and custom fusion workflows. Assets from SPOT 5 have a pixel size of 5m and assets from SPOT 2 and 4 have a pixel size of 10m.\n\n\n### Data access\n\nTo access this dataset, please fill out the [request form](https://forms.gle/jQmCbWgarjENQBYz6).\n",
